To use the bot:
0. Your machine: Make sure you have a copy of this repo.
1. Web browser: Create an app under https://discordapp.com/developers/applications
2. Web browser: Click on the bot tab on the left
3. Web browser: Create a bot, name it, and put a pretty picture on it.
4. Web browser: Copy the token
5. Your machine: Edit config.json, putting the token between the "s where it says "INSERT TOKEN HERE", e.g. "MYSECRETTOKEN"
6. Note: Don't tell anyone your token. Don't show anyone your token. If you do either of these things, generate a new one in the same place you copied it from.
7. Note: You will need Manage Server permissions on whatever server you are trying to join.
8. Web browser: Click the Oauth2 tab.
9. Web browser: Tick the box that says 'bot' and click copy.
10. Web browser: Paste the link you just copied.
11. Web browser: Select the server you wish to add your bot to.
12. Web browser: Tick the box that says you're not a robot. Even if you are.
13. Discord server: Go to the server you added the bot to and say !hello

Based on https://github.com/d0tcc/Secret-Blue
